ed fraction reaches a minimum in all energy bands, and the\nhardness ratios in both NICER and GBM show a turn-over to softening as the\nintensity increases. This behavior repeats as the outburst rises and fades,\nindicating two distinct accretion regimes. These two regimes are suggestive of\nthe accretion structure on the neutron star surface transitioning from a\nCoulomb collisional stopping mechanism at lower luminosities to a\nradiation-dominated stopping mechanism at higher luminosities. This is the\nhighest observed (to date) value of the critical luminosity, suggesting a\nmagnetic field of B ~1E+13 G.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Jun 2018 16:20:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-15"}
